Reasoning: The paper deals with the design and analysis of LDPC codes, which are commonly studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Information Theory and Probability (cs.ITP) sub-categories. The use of spatial coupling techniques also suggests a possible fit with the Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the study of the constraint length of LDPC codes is related to the field of Coding and Information Theory (cs.CC).
